# KoeCraft Agent Rules

You are working on KoeCraft Agent.

Before implementation, inspect:
- `docs/spec.md`
- `docs/architecture.md`
- `docs/harness.md`
- `docs/loop-engineering.md`

Never generate or execute Minecraft world-editing commands such as `/give`, `/fill`, `/setblock`, `/tp`, `/summon`, `/kill`.

The project must use Action DSL and Safety Filter before any Minecraft-side execution.

Keep the LLM role narrow:
- LLM may parse user intent.
- LLM may explain choices.
- LLM must not directly solve recipes from memory.
- LLM must not directly produce executable Minecraft commands.

Use fixtures for behavior changes.

After changes, run the relevant harness command:
```bash
make agent-check
```
